{"type":"step-attempt","step":"design","sessionId":"2e2094e7-430f-4cad-b4b5-656fd12db6b6","outcome":{"verdict":"success","findingsPath":null,"error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"reason":"Wrote design.md, spec.md, and tasks.md under specrunner/changes/round-invalidation-source-scoped/ on branch change/round-invalidation-source-scoped-b69f41a6.\n\nDesign summary:\n- D1: Fix approvedAtCommit's meaning as \"reviewed source revision\" via a contract test — the value is the HEAD captured after member execution but before commitRoundArtifacts (findings commit), which is de-facto already the case under roundOwnsGitEffects. No implementation change to the capture site; a stateful-fake contract test pins the ordering so a regression to meaning (b) fails.\n- D2: Add a pure filter excludeChangeFolderPaths(files) in src/core/pipeline/round-git-scope.ts that drops paths under changesDirRel() (= specrunner/changes/), and apply it at the invalidation site in parallel-review-round.ts between listChangedFiles and computeInvalidations. listChangedFiles seam and computeInvalidations logic are unchanged, so scope.ts / runtime-capability-gate.ts consumers are unaffected. Reuses the readSourceRevision :(exclude)specrunner/changes/ principle; distinct from pipelineManagedPaths (3-file subset) because findings files must also be excluded.\n- D3: computeInvalidations / evaluateActivation / always-activate behavior unchanged → true source changes (src/**) still invalidate (req 3); always-activate (activationPaths undefined) still always invalidates even when source-scoped touched is empty (req 4, behavior preserved); broad-activation reviewers no longer self-invalidate on findings-only changes (req 2, main goal).\n\nTasks: T-01 pure filter + unit test (boundary: same-prefix sibling retained), T-02 wire filter at invalidation site, T-03 approvedAtCommit contract test, T-04 invalidation behavior tests (req 2/3/4), T-05 verification (typecheck+test green, listChangedFiles seam & scope-check tests unchanged, changes limited to round-git-scope.ts + parallel-review-round.ts + their tests). No architecture/ or ADR edits (contract/behavior only, per ADR-20260713 teeth/contract split).","status":"success"},"followUpAttempts":0,"transientRetryAttempts":0,"addedTurns":{"reportRetry":0,"postWork":0,"outputRepair":0}},"startedAt":"2026-07-15T02:07:24.336Z","endedAt":"2026-07-15T02:15:57.367Z"}
